        Kitchens Installed in Leamington Spa
      </h2>
      <div class="gallery-leamington">
        <div style="overflow: hidden; border-radius: 0.5rem;">
          <img
            src="/assets/kitchen-fitter/kitchen-fitter-leamington-spa-navy-kitchen-island-warwickshire-3024x4032.webp"
            alt="Kitchen fitter Leamington Spa — navy blue island kitchen installed in Royal Leamington Spa, Warwickshire"
            width="3024"
            height="4032"
            loading="lazy"
            style="width: 100%; height: 100%; object-fit: cover; display: block;"
          />
        </div>
        <div style="overflow: hidden; border-radius: 0.5rem;">
          <img
            src="/assets/kitchen-fitter/kitchen-fitter-leamington-spa-white-marble-island-kitchen-3024x4032.webp"
            alt="Kitchen fitter Leamington Spa — white kitchen with marble island worktop fitted in Leamington Spa CV31"
            width="3024"
            height="4032"
            loading="lazy"
            style="width: 100%; height: 100%; object-fit: cover; display: block;"
          />
        </div>
        <div style="overflow: hidden; border-radius: 0.5rem;">
          <img
            src="/assets/kitchen-fitter/kitchen-fitter-leamington-spa-gloss-kitchen-install-warwickshire-4032x3024.webp"
            alt="Kitchen fitter Leamington Spa — gloss fitted kitchen installation in Royal Leamington Spa, Warwickshire"
            width="4032"
            height="3024"
            loading="lazy"
            style="width: 100%; height: 100%; object-fit: cover; display: block;"
          />
        </div>
      </div>
      <style>
        .gallery-leamington {
          display: grid;
          grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
          gap: 1rem;
        }
        @media (max-width: 640px) {
          .gallery-leamington {
            grid-template-columns: 1fr;
          }
        }
      </style>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 1: Independent vs Retailer Fitters -->
  <section class="section" style="background: var(--bg-light);">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="max-w-3xl fade-up">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4" style="color: var(--navy);">
          Why Leamington Spa Homeowners Choose an Independent Kitchen Fitter
        </h2>
        <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed mb-4" style="color: var(--text-soft);">
          When you order a kitchen from a retailer, installation is usually offered as an add-on. It sounds straightforward, but the fitters working under retailer schemes are contractors paid to work at pace and to the retailer's specification — not yours. If a wall turns out to be badly out of plumb, or the floor level under your kitchen tiles is uneven, the retailer's fitter does not have the time or incentive to manage it properly.
        </p>
        <p class="leading-relaxed mb-4" style="color: var(--text-soft);">
          In Leamington Spa this matters more than in most towns. The Regency and Victorian housing stock means period property challenges are the norm, not the exception. A fitter who arrives without having surveyed the room, and without the experience to adapt, is unlikely to produce a result you will be happy with in a 180-year-old terrace.
        </p>
        <p class="leading-relaxed mb-4" style="color: var(--text-soft);">
          Pindi Sahota works directly for you. He surveys your specific room before anything is ordered, builds a fixed-price quote based on actual conditions, and carries out the installation himself. There is no call-centre complaints process, no contractor chain, and no incentive to rush.
        </p>
        <p class="leading-relaxed" style="color: var(--text-soft);">
          Independent fitting also means freedom of retailer choice. Pindi fits kitchens from every supplier, so you can buy from whoever suits your budget and style — whether that is IKEA, Wren, Howdens, or a premium brand — without any obligation to use a retailer's own installation service.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 2: Period Properties in Leamington Spa -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="max-w-3xl fade-up">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4" style="color: var(--navy);">
          Fitting Kitchens in Leamington Spa's Period Housing Stock
        </h2>
        <p class="leading-relaxed mb-4" style="color: var(--text-soft);">
          Royal Leamington Spa is one of the most architecturally intact Regency towns in England. The conservation area and the surrounding streets contain a concentration of period properties that is unusual even by Warwickshire standards — Regency terraces and villas from the 1820s to 1840s, large Victorian semi-detached properties on the Kenilworth Road side of the town, and densely built Victorian mid-terraces across Milverton and parts of Lillington.
        </p>
        <p class="leading-relaxed mb-4" style="color: var(--text-soft);">
          Each of these property types presents fitting challenges that reward an experienced, prepared tradesperson. In Regency terraces, walls that were never intended to carry fitted furniture can be 40mm or more out of plumb from floor to ceiling — a fact that only becomes apparent once base units are being set out and the gap between cabinet top and wall begins to grow. Victorian kitchens, particularly those that were originally sculleries converted into modern kitchen spaces, often feature narrow room widths, low ceiling heights, and original stone or quarry tile floors beneath later kitchen tile layers that can cause levelling problems when the old kitchen is stripped.
        </p>
        <p class="leading-relaxed mb-4" style="color: var(--text-soft);">
          Pindi has fitted kitchens across Leamington's period housing, including an IKEA METOD installation in a Victorian mid-terrace in the town — a project that required careful floor levelling and scribing to manage a significantly out-of-square room. That hands-on local experience is what the <a href="/projects/ikea-kitchen-leamington-spa/" class="font-semibold" style="color: var(--teal);">Leamington Spa IKEA project</a> demonstrates in practice.
        </p>
        <p class="leading-relaxed" style="color: var(--text-soft);">
          Modern apartment blocks closer to the town centre present a different set of considerations: access, delivery logistics, and building regulations compliance for ventilation and electrics. Pindi has experience across all of Leamington's property types and plans for the specific constraints of each.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 3: The Survey-First Process -->
  <section class="section" style="background: var(--bg-light);">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="max-w-3xl fade-up">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4" style="color: var(--navy);">
          The Survey-First Process — Essential for Leamington Period Properties
        </h2>
        <p class="leading-relaxed mb-4" style="color: var(--text-soft);">
          Every kitchen fitting project with Pindi begins with a pre-installation survey, carried out personally before anything is ordered. The survey costs £195 and is credited back in full if you proceed with the installation. In Leamington Spa — where period property complications are common — it is not an optional extra. It is how problems are identified and planned for before they become expensive surprises.
        </p>
        <p class="leading-relaxed mb-4" style="color: var(--text-soft);">
          During the survey, Pindi takes precise room measurements, checks ceiling heights and wall plumb, inspects existing plumbing and electrical routes, reviews your kitchen plan and elevation drawings, and identifies any preparatory work required before or alongside the installation. In period properties this routinely includes checking floor levels, testing wall construction before hanging wall units, and assessing whether existing waste and supply pipework positions are compatible with the new kitchen layout.
        </p>
        <p class="leading-relaxed mb-4" style="color: var(--text-soft);">
          After the survey you receive a written, fixed-price quote. The price does not change unless you change the scope of work. There are no surprises on completion day, no additional charges for complications that should have been spotted during planning, and no retrospective claims for extra time.
        </p>
        <p class="leading-relaxed" style="color: var(--text-soft);">
          Survey appointments in Leamington Spa are typically available within two weeks. To book, call <a href="tel:07399651836" class="font-semibold" style="color: var(--teal);">07399 651836</a> or visit the <a href="/survey/" class="font-semibold" style="color: var(--teal);">survey booking page</a>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

